went up the water spout *

38:09.080 --> 38:13.793
* Down came the rain
and washed the spider out *

38:17.922 --> 38:21.009
* Up came the sun *

38:21.051 --> 38:23.636
* Dried up all the rain *

38:23.678 --> 38:28.391
* The itsy bitsy spider
went up the spout *

38:28.433 --> 38:30.518
[yawning] Again.

38:36.107 --> 38:39.069
* Went up the water spout *

38:41.112 --> 38:44.616
* And dried up all the rain *

38:44.657 --> 38:50.038
* The itsy bitsy spider *

38:50.080 --> 38:53.124
* Went up the spout again *

38:54.584 --> 38:58.922
* The itsy bitsy spider *

38:58.963 --> 39:01.925
* Down came the rain *

39:01.966 --> 39:07.013
* And washed the spider out *

39:08.807 --> 39:13.353
* Up came the sun and *

39:17.941 --> 39:20.151
"Mother and Father."

39:22.654 --> 39:26.950
"You want me to be unheard.

39:26.991 --> 39:29.661
"But I am heard.

39:29.703 --> 39:32.914
You wish me to be unfelt..."

39:32.956 --> 39:35.083
- "But I am felt.

39:35.125 --> 39:37.252
"You thought you made me gone.

39:37.293 --> 39:40.130
"But you failed.

39:40.171 --> 39:42.882
"I'm here,
and I will haunt you.

39:42.924 --> 39:45.427
I will not be gone."

39:45.468 --> 39:48.430
[eerie music]

39:48.471 --> 39:55.395
* *

40:23.548 --> 40:25.675
- What are you going?

40:25.717 --> 40:27.344
What are you doing?
- I--

40:27.385 --> 40:28.386
I was curious

40:28.428 --> 40:30.305
as to your writing project,
so...

40:30.347 --> 40:33.558
why is there
a letter from Vincent

40:33.600 --> 40:35.477
to his parents?

40:35.518 --> 40:39.105
What's going on?
- I--I wrote that.

40:39.147 --> 40:41.941
- No, these are handwritten
by him.

40:41.983 --> 40:44.944
I know Vincent's handwriting.

40:44.986 --> 40:48.573
"I will not be gone.
I will haunt you."

40:48.615 --> 40:50.533
- I--I can explain that.

40:50.575 --> 40:51.993
- Really?
- Yes.

40:52.035 --> 40:54.120
- Well, you better start.

40:56.456 --> 41:00.627
- The handwritten materials
were written by Vincent, yes.

41:00.669 --> 41:02.837
We were going over
his college essays,

41:02.879 --> 41:06.591
and I was encouraging him to,
you know, dig a little deeper,

41:06.633 --> 41:10.512
which you can obviously see
that he did.

41:10.553 --> 41:14.391
The stuff on the computer,
I wrote that.

41:14.432 --> 41:15.558
- Why?

41:15.600 --> 41:17.394
- For class.

41:17.435 --> 41:19.020
- For class?

41:19.062 --> 41:20.939
- Yes, Michael wanted me
to be more authentic.

41:20.980 --> 41:23.858
He told me that my writing
didn't feel real,

41:23.900 --> 41:27.445
so I just appropriated
some of Vincent's feelings,

41:27.487 --> 41:30.615
some of Vincent's thoughts,
and I used them in my--

41:30.657 --> 41:35.036
put them in my...you know?

41:35.078 --> 41:38.498
- I don't understand.

41:38.540 --> 41:40.542
- You don't underst--
look, I just--

41:40.583 --> 41:44.963
I needed to...climb
into the inside of something,

41:45.005 --> 41:47.632
so I decided
to get inside Vincent,

41:47.674 --> 41:51.594
to figure out, if he ran away,
why he would run away.

41:51.636 --> 41:54.014
It's fiction.
Honey, I made it up.

41:54.055 --> 41:55.557
It's nothing.
- This is sick.

41:55.598 --> 41:58.393
- This is what writers do.
We channel.

41:58.435 --> 41:59.644
Kafka, Sondheim.

41:59.686 --> 42:01.563
They look into the souls
of themselves,

42:01.604 --> 42:04.065
into the souls of others,
and they channel.

42:04.107 --> 42:05.859
That's what I was trying to do
with Vincent,

42:05.900 --> 42:10.113
to feel
what he might be feeling.

42:10.155 --> 42:13.742
To get the reader to feel that.
That's all, baby.

42:13.783 --> 42:16.077
It's okay. That's all.

42:16.119 --> 42:19.831
[suspenseful music]

42:19.873 --> 42:22.876
- I don't believe you.

42:22.917 --> 42:24.753
You've done something.

42:26.546 --> 42:30.592
You've done something
to Vincent.

42:30.633 --> 42:36.181
